    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The global module state implementation introduced in #3223 needs to be cleaned up.\r\n\r\n- [ ] Always use a module state struct, not only for the limited API / `CYTHON_USE_MODULE_STATE` case.\r\n- [ ] Remove the long `#define x state->x` blocks at the beginning of the module code and replace them by lookup macros for globals that also use `__pyx_self` in all places where it's available, since that's what the lookups will be based on in the future. Examples: `__Pyx_GlobalInCyFunction(__pyx_self, global_name)` and `__Pyx_GlobalInInit(__pyx_m, global_name)` etc.\r\n- [ ] Merge the duplicate cleanup functions.\r\n\r\nNote that this cleanup needs to be based on #3611.",
